snippet.title: We are a 'Dry State' | Comedy | Dreamz Unlimited
snippet.description:
Nagaland Liquor Total Prohibition (NLTP) Act, 1989 was passed on Nagaland Legislative Assembly in 1989. Those who support alcohol prohibition point at the dangers of drinking, the lives it has destroyed and the misery caused. They no doubt have a point, but some countered that alcohol consumption should be regulated in public interest, and not totally prohibited.
Nevertheless, Nagaland became a ‚Äòdry state‚Äô and instead of drinking legally, people started drinking ‚Äòillegally.‚Äô
The inflow of liquor into the dry state has since remained regular and adequate for the consumers over the last 31 years and hundreds of people are arrested every year for ‚Äúcontravention of the provision‚Äù of the Act.
This video is a satire take on the subject.

snippet.title: True Facts: The Incredible Tardigrade
snippet.description:
True Facts Shirts: https://ze-true-store.myshopify.com/
Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/truefacts
Sign up for Curiosity Stream: https://curiositystream.com/zefrank

CREDITS:

This video was made in collaboration with Benedikt Pleyer, who is a gifted microscopist and has a wonderful contagious passion for discovering the incredible worlds that exist all around us. He has introduced me to all sorts of new creatures and I am fortunate to have met him. 
http://www.instagram.com/nomadic_nostoc

Kita Williams reached out to me almost a year ago with her amazing Tardigrade footage, and I am so happy that she did. She has a knack for capturing these animals in way that gives them so much personality!
http://www.twitter.com/SeaSpongeCake

Bob Goldstein runs a lab at UNC Chapel Hill and has done incredible work on the Tardigrade (and much more.) He was kind enough to review my work to make sure I didn't screw the science up too much! I wish I could have included more of his work on the evolution of Tardigrades - but I hope to do that in a future episode on arthropods.
https://goldsteinlab.weebly.com/

snippet.description:
Today AD is welcomed by tennis legend and 23-time Grand Slam singles title winner Serena Williams for a tour of her stunning new home north of Miami. After living with her sister Venus on and off for over 20 years, Serena and husband Alexis Ohanian have made a stylish new home for their family. From the eclectic artwork (including her own painting) to the world-beating trophy room, Serena‚Äôs home could only belong to someone as multifaceted and accomplished as her. ‚ÄúI was moving away from Venus for the first time in my life, so I wanted it to be really meaningful,‚Äù Serena says. While mixing family with business can be risky, the secret to their success as siblings and creative collaborators is simple: ‚ÄúYou have to know your lane. I‚Äôm really good at playing tennis; I‚Äôm not as good at interiors. But I was able to learn through just watching Venus.‚Äù

snippet.title: Claire Saffitz Makes Confetti Cake | Dessert Person
snippet.description:
Claire Saffitz Makes Confetti Cake | Dessert Person. Get ready to party! And by party, we mean stay at home and be safe. But fortunately, you need no special occasion to make this delicious, celebratory, kid-friendly, and deeply nostalgic confetti cake. A tender white birthday cake studded with rainbow sprinkles and covered in smooth, tangy cream cheese frosting, it tastes like childhood (which is to say, better than the box). We took a hiatus but Claire and her crew are back with Season II of Dessert Person -- check out this first episode!

#ClaireSaffitz‚Äã #DessertPerson‚Äã #Cake‚Äã

Special Equipment:
Stand mixer
Three 9-inch cake pans

Ingredients:

Confetti Cake:
Butter for the pans
5 1/2 cups cake flour (23.3 oz/ 660g)
2 1/2 cups sugar (16.4 oz / 466g)
4 1/2 teaspoons baking powder (0.63 oz / 18g)
1 1/2 teaspoons Diamond Crystal kosher salt (0.16 oz / 5g)
3/4 teaspoon baking soda
3 sticks unsalted butter (12 oz / 340g), at room temperature
1 1/2 cups buttermilk (12.7 oz / 360g)
1/3 cup neutral oil, such as vegetable or grapeseed (2.6 oz / 75g)
3 large eggs (5.3 oz / 150g), at room temperature
6 large egg whites (7.4 oz / 210g), at room temperature
1 tablespoon vanilla extract
1/2 teaspoon almond extract (optional)
1/2 cup store-bought rainbow sprinkles (3.3 oz / 93g), plus more for decorating
Classic Cream Cheese Frosting

snippet.title: Barcelona stages SENSATIONAL comeback vs. Granada to reach Copa del Rey semis | ESPN FC Highlights
snippet.description:
Lionel Messi and Barcelona had their backs against the wall once again in the Copa del Rey facing a two-goal deficit for much of their quarterfinal vs. Granada. The hosts went in front with goals from Robert Kenedy and Roberto Soldado. Barca left its comeback late with goals in the 88th minute and stoppage time from Antoine Griezmann and Jordi Alba. The game went to extra time where the two sides traded goals from Griezmann and Fede Vico, but in the second extra time period Alba and Frenkie de Jong seal the victory for the Blaugrana. Barcelona advances to the Copa del Rey semifinals for the 10th time in the last 11 seasons, with its only elimination before the semis coming last season.

snippet.description:
NUGGETS at LAKERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | February 4, 2021

LeBron James put up a huge triple-double with 27 PTS, 10 REB and 10 AST as the Los Angeles Lakers defeated the Denver Nuggets, 114-93. Dennis Schroder netted 21 PTS and 4 AST, Talen Horton-Tucker provided 17 PTS and Anthony Davis finished with 13 PTS, 9 REB, 3 STL and 2 BLK in the win. Jamal Murray led the Nuggets with 20 PTS and 5 AST, and Nikola Jokic finished with 13 PTS, 10 REB and 6 AST.

my MATHEMATICAL flow that‚Äôs ADDS me in every room but me SUBTRACTS me from the trash that they‚Äôve been force feeding to you

fucking up GIANTS, DAVID you‚Äôre GOLIATH

wanna be me the only thing you‚Äôll ever (B)-is-HEPATITIS

snippet.title: 16-year-old detained under Singapore's Internal Security Act after planning to attack two mosques
snippet.description:
A 16-year-old has been detained under Singapore's Internal Security Act. He had planned to attack Muslims at two local mosques on the second anniversary of the Christchurch attacks on March 15. The authorities said the secondary school student is the youngest to be detained under the act, and the first to be inspired by far-right extremist ideology. The youth is a Protestant Christian of Indian ethnicity. He had planned to attack Muslims at Assyafaah Mosque and Yusof Ishak Mosque. The mosques are about 4km apart and located near his home.

snippet.title: LEEDS UNITED 1-2 EVERTON | PREMIER LEAGUE HIGHLIGHTS
snippet.description:
Everton made it four away wins a row with a 2-1 victory at Leeds United. Gylfi Sigurdsson opened the scoring for Carlo Ancelotti's Blues, before DCL headed a second just before the break. Raphinha pulled one back for the hosts, but Marcelo Bielsa's side couldn't find an equaliser and the Toffees went home with all three points!

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures comes the long-awaited face-off between two icons, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù the next epic adventure in Legendary‚Äôs cinematic Monsterverse, directed by Adam Wingard.

Legends collide in ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong‚Äù as these mythic adversaries meet in a spectacular battle for the ages, with the fate of the world hanging in the balance.  Kong and his protectors undertake a perilous journey to find his true home, and with them is Jia, a young orphaned girl with whom he has formed a unique and powerful bond.  But they unexpectedly find themselves in the path of an enraged Godzilla, cutting a swath of destruction across the globe.  The epic clash between the two titans‚Äîinstigated by unseen forces‚Äîis only the beginning of the mystery that lies deep within the core of the Earth.

The film stars Alexander Skarsg√•rd (‚ÄúBig Little Lies,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Little Drummer Girl‚Äù), Millie Bobby Brown (‚ÄúStranger Things‚Äù), Rebecca Hall (‚ÄúChristine,‚Äù ‚ÄúProfessor Marston and the Wonder Women‚Äù), Brian Tyree Henry (‚ÄúJoker,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse‚Äù), Shun Oguri (‚ÄúWeathering with You‚Äù), Eiza Gonz√°lez (‚ÄúFast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw‚Äù), Julian Dennison (‚ÄúDeadpool 2‚Äù), with Kyle Chandler (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù) and Demi√°n Bichir (‚ÄúThe Nun,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Hateful Eight‚Äù).
Wingard (‚ÄúThe Guest,‚Äù ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre Next‚Äù) directed from a screenplay by Eric Pearson (‚ÄúThor: Ragnarok‚Äù) and Max Borenstein (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters,‚Äù ‚ÄúKong: Skull Island‚Äù), story by Terry Rossio (‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales‚Äù) and Michael Dougherty & Zach Shields (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), based on the character ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù owned and created by TOHO CO., LTD.  The film was produced by Mary Parent, Alex Garcia, Eric McLeod, Jon Jashni, Thomas Tull and Brian Rogers, with Jay Ashenfelter, Herbert W. Gains, Dan Lin, Roy Lee, Yoshimitsu Banno and Kenji Okuhira executive producing.

The director‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team included director of photography Ben Seresin (‚ÄúThe Mummy,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld War Z‚Äù), production designers Owen Paterson (‚ÄúJumanji: Welcome to the Jungle,‚Äù ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù) and Thomas S. Hammock (‚ÄúBlair Witch‚Äù), editor Josh Schaeffer (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), costume designer Ann Foley (‚ÄúSkyscraper‚Äù) and visual effects supervisor John ‚ÄúDJ‚Äù DesJardin (upcoming ‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, A Film By Adam Wingard, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong.‚Äù  The film will be released nationwide in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX on March 26, 2021 and will be available in the U.S. on HBO Max for 31 days from theatrical release.  It is rated PG-13 for intense sequences of creature violence/destruction and brief language.

snippet.title: Myanmar leaders Aung San Suu Kyi, President Win Myint and others detained in raids | ABC News
snippet.description:
Myanmar leader Aung San Suu Kyi has been detained in an early morning raid along with other senior ruling party figures.
Subscribe: http://ab.co/1svxLVE  Read more here: https://ab.co/3j62Cud
The South-East Asian nation's new parliament was due to meet today for the first time since the November election, which was won in a landslide by Aung San Suu Kyi's party, but which the military says was marred by fraud.
National League for Democracy (NLD) spokesman Myo Nyunt said Ms Suu Kyi, President Win Myint and other leaders had been "taken" in the early hours of the morning.

snippet.title: Godzilla vs. Kong ‚Äì Official Trailer
snippet.description:
In theaters and streaming exclusively on @HBOMax* March 26.
¬†

---

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures comes the long-awaited face-off between two icons, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù the next epic adventure in Legendary‚Äôs cinematic Monsterverse, directed by Adam Wingard.

Legends collide in ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong‚Äù as these mythic adversaries meet in a spectacular battle for the ages, with the fate of the world hanging in the balance.  Kong and his protectors undertake a perilous journey to find his true home, and with them is Jia, a young orphaned girl with whom he has formed a unique and powerful bond.  But they unexpectedly find themselves in the path of an enraged Godzilla, cutting a swath of destruction across the globe.  The epic clash between the two titans‚Äîinstigated by unseen forces‚Äîis only the beginning of the mystery that lies deep within the core of the Earth.

The film stars Alexander Skarsg√•rd (‚ÄúBig Little Lies,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Little Drummer Girl‚Äù), Millie Bobby Brown (‚ÄúStranger Things‚Äù), Rebecca Hall (‚ÄúChristine,‚Äù ‚ÄúProfessor Marston and the Wonder Women‚Äù), Brian Tyree Henry (‚ÄúJoker,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse‚Äù), Shun Oguri (‚ÄúWeathering with You‚Äù), Eiza Gonz√°lez (‚ÄúFast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw‚Äù), Julian Dennison (‚ÄúDeadpool 2‚Äù), with Kyle Chandler (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù) and Demi√°n Bichir (‚ÄúThe Nun,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Hateful Eight‚Äù).
Wingard (‚ÄúThe Guest,‚Äù ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre Next‚Äù) directed from a screenplay by Eric Pearson (‚ÄúThor: Ragnarok‚Äù) and Max Borenstein (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters,‚Äù ‚ÄúKong: Skull Island‚Äù), story by Terry Rossio (‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales‚Äù) and Michael Dougherty & Zach Shields (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), based on the character ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù owned and created by TOHO CO., LTD.  The film was produced by Mary Parent, Alex Garcia, Eric McLeod, Jon Jashni, Thomas Tull and Brian Rogers, with Jay Ashenfelter, Herbert W. Gains, Dan Lin, Roy Lee, Yoshimitsu Banno and Kenji Okuhira executive producing.

The director‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team included director of photography Ben Seresin (‚ÄúThe Mummy,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld War Z‚Äù), production designers Owen Paterson (‚ÄúJumanji: Welcome to the Jungle,‚Äù ‚ÄúGodzilla‚Äù) and Thomas S. Hammock (‚ÄúBlair Witch‚Äù), editor Josh Schaeffer (‚ÄúGodzilla: King of the Monsters‚Äù), costume designer Ann Foley (‚ÄúSkyscraper‚Äù) and visual effects supervisor John ‚ÄúDJ‚Äù DesJardin (upcoming ‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, A Film By Adam Wingard, ‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong.‚Äù  The film will be released nationwide in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX on March 26, 2021 and will be available in the U.S. on HBO Max for 31 days from theatrical release.  It is rated PG-13 for intense sequences of creature violence/destruction and brief language.

snippet.title: The Devil wears Dior: Where is Melissa Caddick and the missing millions? | 60 Minutes Australia
snippet.description:
Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | The Devil wears Dior (2021)

By all accounts Melissa Caddick loved the good things in life. And splashing cash on anything she wanted was never a problem. She was loaded. Caddick always looked a million bucks in her designer clothes, she travelled first class everywhere, and called a stunning Sydney mansion home. She claimed her wealth was the result of her brilliance in business, and generously for her friends and family, she offered to share her financial secrets. The deal she proposed to them was simple: if they trusted her with their retirement savings, everyone would win. But it was a lie. Eleven weeks ago, Melissa Caddick and twenty million dollars of money that wasn‚Äôt hers suddenly vanished.
 
Tom Steinfort reports the latest developments in the police search for Caddick; traces her last known moments before she disappeared; interviews the former friends who were duped after entrusting her with their hard-earned savings; and asks Caddick‚Äôs husband, Anthony Koletti, about the accusations against his wife.

snippet.title: Starship | SN9 | High-Altitude Flight Test
snippet.description:
On Tuesday, February 2, Starship serial number 9 (SN9) completed SpaceX‚Äôs second high-altitude flight test of a Starship prototype from our site in Cameron County, Texas.

Similar to the high-altitude flight test of Starship serial number 8 (SN8), SN9 was powered through ascent by three Raptor engines, each shutting down in sequence prior to the vehicle reaching apogee ‚Äì approximately 10 kilometers in altitude. SN9 successfully performed a propellant transition to the internal header tanks, which hold landing propellant, before reorienting itself for reentry and a controlled aerodynamic descent.

The Starship prototype descended under active aerodynamic control, accomplished by independent movement of two forward and two aft flaps on the vehicle. All four flaps are actuated by an onboard flight computer to control Starship‚Äôs attitude during flight and enable precise landing at the intended location. During the landing flip maneuver, one of the Raptor engines did not relight and caused SN9 to land at high speed and experience a RUD.

These test flights are all about improving our understanding and development of a fully reusable transportation system designed to carry both crew and cargo on long-duration, interplanetary flights and help humanity return to the Moon, and travel to Mars and beyond.

snippet.description:
I got the chance to interview Bill Gates so I asked him: Will Covid-19 be the last pandemic? How does he deal with misinformation and conspiracy theories? And what is the next disaster? The Foundation Letter is here: https://ve42.co/BG21

Special thanks to Patreon supporters:
Ludovic Robillard, jim buckmaster, Robert, fanime96, Marc Forand, Juan Benet, Robert Blum, Grace O'Maille KRON x Arc iOS, Richard Sundvall, Lee Redden, Vincent, Lyvann Ferrusca, Alfred Wallace, Arjun Chakroborty, Joar Wandborg, Clayton Greenwell, Pindex , Michael Krugman, Cy 'kkm' K'Nelson, Sam Lutfi, Ron Neal

Thanks to Petr Lebedev for early edits and Jonny Hyman for feedback

snippet.title: Enchanting Tiny House & Gardens On Generational Family Farm
snippet.description:
This spectacular tiny house situated on a multi generational family farm is absolutely breathtaking. Ruby grew up on this farm. The family has a deep connection to this land, and it's where Ruby wanted to deepen her roots by building her own home. 

Not wanting to get into a huge amount of debt, she wanted to keep her home small and simple and a tiny house was the ideal solution. She has added onto the main tiny house structure by creating seperate structures for both a shower / laundry room, as well as a toilet. 

Ruby is a gardener by profession and the area all around her home has been exquisitely planted to create majestic, productive gardens.. Plants even climb the exterior walls of the tiny house which helps to make the home feel even more enchanting. 

This is an amazing tiny house which has been situated in an incredibly special place. We hope you enjoy the full video tour! 

You can follow Ruby's adventures on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/rubyalicewheeler/

Find out more about this tiny house and others on our website: https://www.livingbiginatinyhouse.com/

Follow us on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/livingbiginatinyhouse

Follow us on Facebook:  http://www.facebook.com/livingbiginatinyhouse

Follow us on Twitter: https://twitter.com/tinyhousenz

Please subscribe for more videos on tiny houses, architecture, DIY, design, and sustainable, off-grid living.

Title music in this video by Bryce Langston: http://www.youtube.com/brycelangston

Camera: Rasa Pescud & Bryce Langston

snippet.title: I am so confused.
snippet.description:
Schlatt wonders why his last video got 80,000 comments.

Follow me on Twitter:
https://twitter.com/jschlatt

Follow me on Instagram:
https://instagram.com/jschlatt

Truly disgusting, that some people would do this horrible thing. Why? Why did you comment this? Are you part of the problem? No, I'll tell you what the problem is. The problem is that TommyInnit and the Dream SMP are getting more viewers than me even though I'm so much cooler than everyone else on it (like Ranboo, Awesamdude, Karl Jacobs, and others whose names I forgot). Tubbo is pretty cool I guess though. Schlatt talks about why his latest video got 80,000 comments, which is insane and almost seems like algorithm manipulation (CC: Spiffing Brit). Almost as bad as the algorithm manipulation that writing these meaningless paragraphs contributes to. But hey I'm in it for the money. ToaLegend makes an appearance as well, with his hit classic "Nibble" which will now get millions of comments I bet. Please be nice.

snippet.title: Claus Ruhe Madsen √ºber seinen Weg in der Corona-Pandemie | Markus Lanz vom 03. Februar 2021
snippet.description:
‚ÄûWir m√ºssen den Menschen einen Weg vorzeigen, eine Perspektive geben‚Äú, sagt der Oberb√ºrger-meister Rostocks Claus Ruhe Madsen. Man sei von Seite der Bundesregierung aus unehrlich zu den B√ºrgerinnen und B√ºrgern gewesen. Seiner Meinung nach sei die Reihenfolge w√§hrend des Lockdowns eine falsche gewesen. Man h√§tte zu aller erst die Kontaktbeschr√§nkungen erh√∂hen sollen, bevor man die Einzelhandelsl√§den, Fris√∂re, Kinos und Kulturst√§tten schlie√üt. Er erkl√§rt, dass man Kontakte im √∂ffentlichen R√§umen wesentlich besser kontrollieren k√∂nne, wie in einem Restaurant mit Listen zum Nachverfolgen, als im privaten zu Hause, wo trotzdem Feiern mit vielen Menschen stattfinden w√ºrden.
Seine Politik sei daher gewesen: Konsequent von Anfang an die Pandemie bek√§mpfen, bevor sie √ºberhaupt richtig begonnen habe. Aufgrund dieser Strategie, erkl√§rt er, seien die Infektions- und Todeszahlen in Rostock im Vergleich zur restlichen Bundesrepublik sehr niedrig.
Zudem berichtet er √ºber seine Erfahrung mit dem Robert Koch Institut, welches ihn gebeten hatte bei dem Aufbau von Testkapazit√§ten in Rostock auf die Vorschl√§ge zu achten, die diese f√ºr die Bundesrepublik vorgaben, da er schon deutlich h√∂her auffahren wollte.


Den gesamten Talk findet ihr hier: https://kurz.zdf.de/8FR/
 
Weitere G√§ste in der Sendung:

Christoph R√∂ckerath, Journalist
Der Leiter des ZDF-Studios Rio de Janeiro berichtet direkt aus Brasilien, wo sich aufgrund einer Coronavirus-Mutation das Infektionsgeschehen dramatisch zuspitzt.
 
Prof. Hendrik Streeck, Virologe
Er erkl√§rt, wie Virusmutationen entstehen und inwieweit bereits vorhandene Impfstoffe gegen sie wirken. Und er √§u√üert sich zur Wahrscheinlichkeit einer dritten Infektionswelle.  
 
Vanessa Vu, Journalistin
Die ‚ÄûZeit Online‚Äú-Redakteurin analysiert das Agieren von Bundes- und L√§nderpolitikern. Sie meint: ‚ÄûDiese Kleinstaaterei ist vielen Menschen nicht mehr vermittelbar und unverst√§ndlich.‚Äú
 
Manfred Weber, Politiker
Der CSU-Politiker und Fraktionschef der EVP im Europaparlament nimmt Stellung zum Vorgehen der EU-Kommission bei der Impfstoffbeschaffung und zur weiteren Impfstrategie.

_____
Hier auf ZDFheute Nachrichten erfahrt ihr, was auf der Welt passiert und was uns alle etwas an-geht: Wir sorgen f√ºr Durchblick in der Nachrichtenwelt, erkl√§ren die Hintergr√ºnde und gehen auf gesellschaftliche Debatten ein. Diskutiert in Livestreams mit uns und bildet euch eure eigene Meinung mit den Fakten, die wir euch pr√§sentieren.

Abonniert unseren Kanal, um nichts mehr zu verpassen.

Immer auf dem aktuellen Stand seid ihr auf http://www.ZDFheute.de/.

snippet.title: Mord an ‚ÄûKranken" ‚Äì ‚ÄûEuthanasie" im Nationalsozialismus
snippet.description:
‚ÄûEuthanasie‚Äú ‚Äì so nannten die Nationalsozialisten die systematische Ermordung von Menschen mit k√∂rperlicher Behinderung oder mit psychischen Erkrankungen. Der Begriff Euthanasie kommt aus dem Griechischen und bedeutet soviel wie ‚Äûsch√∂ner Tod‚Äú oder auch ‚Äûleichter Tod‚Äú. Heute ist der harmlos erscheinende Begriff untrennbar mit den Gr√§ueltaten der Nazis verbunden, die w√§hrend ihrer Herrschaft rund 300.000 k√∂rperlich behinderte und psychisch erkrankte Menschen in verschiedenen Vernichtungsprogrammen umgebracht haben. Das bekannteste Programm ist die ‚ÄûAktion T4‚Äú ‚Äì dieser Aktion allein fallen √ºber 70.000 Menschen zum Opfer. Der Tarnname T4 leitet sich von der Adresse Tiergartenstra√üe 4 in Berlin ab.
